[00:19.85]but as the oceans have been overfished, fish has become more and more expensive.|但由于海洋过度捕捞，鱼类的价格越来越高。
[00:27.29]So it comes as a surprise to learn that giant fish are terrifying the divers on North Sea oil rigs.|因此，当人们得知巨大的鱼类正在让北海石油钻井平台的潜水员感到恐惧时，确实感到十分惊讶。
[00:37.30]Oil rigs have to be repaired frequently and divers, who often have to work in darkness a hundred feet under water,|这些石油钻井平台需要频繁维修，而潜水员往往必须在百英尺深的水下工作；
[00:47.27]have been frightened out of their wits by giant fish bumping into them as they work.|巨大的鱼类在潜水员作业时突然撞上他们，让他们惊恐万分。
[00:54.83]Now they have had special cages made to protect them from these monsters.|现在，人们专门为潜水员制造了防护笼子来保护他们免受这些鱼类的伤害。
[01:01.06]The fish are not sharks or killer whales,|这些鱼既不是鲨鱼，也不是虎鲸，
